         <h3>
            11. After demonstrating the feasibility of MIX, then what?
         </h3>
         <div class="content">
            <p>
               We will design and build a prototype unit, demonstrating useful power production.
            </p>
            <p>
               The resulting technology can then be licensed to a strategic energy industry player, like <acronym title="General Electric">GE</acronym>, or we can raise money on the capital markets
               to start scale production.
            </p>
            <p>
               Fusion power from a MIX-derived machine would cost significantly less than conventionally generated electricity. Under pessimistic assumptions, IEC energy would cost no more than one
               tenth of conventionally generated power, and will most likely cost even less.
            </p>
            <p>
               The global energy market is currently worth about USD 5 trillion. Commercially viable IEC fusion reactors would capture most of this market.
            </p>
